# **PLS UPVOTE 👍**
# Approach
- **Using hash function, characters of string are stored and when count exceeds more than one, reset the count and increment answer by 1**.

---

<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N) 

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int partitionString(string s) {
        int n = s.size();

        vector<int>hsh(26,0);
        int cnt = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            if(hsh[s[i]-'a'] != 0)
            {
                cnt++;
                for(int i = 0; i < 26; i++)
                {
                    hsh[i] = 0; // reset all count to 0
                }
                hsh[s[i]-'a']++;
            }
            else
            {
                hsh[s[i]-'a']++;
            }
        }

        return cnt+1; //add 1 to store last string partition
    }
};
```

