# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We are using hash array to check if element appeared before or not

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Take a hash array boolean type and fill it with false value at all the places
We are cheking if a character appeared before if yes increment ans by one and fill hash array with false else we can make true in hash array at valid position 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We are traversing string once so the time complexity is O(N)
O(N)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We are using extra 26 size boolean array (Constant space) so that space complexity is O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int partitionString(String s) {
        boolean []hash = new boolean[26];
        Arrays.fill(hash,false);

        int i = 0,ans = 1;
        while(i<s.length()){
            int n = s.charAt(i)-'a';
            if(hash[n]==true){
                Arrays.fill(hash,false);
                ans++;
            }
            hash[n] = true;
            i++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```
