# Intuition
We just have to count substrings which have no duplicate characters.

# Approach
If the string length is 1, then obviously answer is 1.

Else we have to count the no of distinct substrings.

We start by creating a set which will store distinct characters encountered till current time.

Initially we insert the first character s[0] into the set.
We then run a loop from i=1 to i=length-1 
which will check if the current character is not present in the set.
In that case we will insert that character into the set.

Else if that character is found , then we take this as a substring and increment our ans variable.
Then we clear the set and insert the current element into the set.

Our final answer will obviously be ans+1 since we did not increment our ans variable when we were generating our final substring.

Thanks!

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n) for string traversal and O(n) for find() function.
So overall  T.C : O(n).

- Space complexity:
O(n) since we are creating a set which can have at max n elements in the worst case.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int partitionString(string s) {
        int n = s.length();
        if(n==1)
            return 1;

        int ans = 0;
        set<char>freq; 
        freq.insert(s[0]);

        for(int i=1; i<n ;i++){
            if(freq.find(s[i]) == freq.end() )
                freq.insert(s[i]);

            else
            {
                ans++;
                freq.clear();
                freq.insert(s[i]);
            }
        }
        return ans+1;
    }
};
```

