# Intuition
Keep it simple and *don't overcomplicate* this by thinking of sliding window and other concepts. Since the question wants us to find partition input string into substrings when there is a repeating character, its clear that we can simply use ***Hashmap or even Set data structure*** to maintain which character we have already seen.

---


# Approach
1) Intialise Set datastructure
2) Iterate over each character in the input string
2) We will keep adding character to set if it is not present.
3) If the set.contains() return true for a character, we know we have reached a point where duplication of some character has taken place
- so we clear the set since we found a partition.
- increment the substring count i.e count++
4) Keep repeating till string ends
5) Reason why ***count+1 is done***, +1 covers the last substring as well.

---


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n): Since we traverse through entire string.

---

