# Intuition
As we need to find substrings so we could see substrings to be divided as various windows to be seperated . Hence we could keep track of seen characters and as we see a duplicate character appear we can say that here is the place where window will be broken.

# Approach - 1
1. We keep track of seen characters using a set of characters.
2. We keep increasing the window untill we see the characters are different .
3. As soon as we see a character that is same we break , increase count and clear our set for next iteration

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N) * log (26)

- Space complexity: O(26)

# Code - 1
```
class Solution {
public:
    int partitionString(string s) {
        set<char> st;
        int j = 0 , cnt = 0;
        for(int i = 0 ; i < s.size() ; i++){
            while(i < s.size() && st.find(s[i]) == st.end()){
                st.insert(s[i]);
                i++;
            }
            i--;
            cnt++;
            st.clear();
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};
```
# Approach - 2
1. We keep track of characters using a visited array.
2. We keep increasing the window untill we see the characters are different.
3. As soon as we see a character that is same we break , increase count and clear our array for next iteration.
4. we check at the last for any remaining characters.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N * 26)

- Space complexity: O(26)
# Code - 2
