```
/*
    Approach

    As need to make partition by substrings, so the partition must be continuous in the given string
    The substring must be unique and the number of partitions must be minimum

    So, by starting traversing from left-to-right, put characters in a set until you found a character that already present in the set
    If found the character in the set, at this time the characters present in the set forms the longest substring
    now increase the counter and make set empty.

    Ex: s = "abacaba"
    initially, set = { }

    start traversing from left-to-right

    count = 0
    a -> not present in set -> {'a'}
    b -> not present in set -> { 'a', 'b' }
    a -> present in set -> count=1, set { } -> set{'a'} // put current character n set for future 
    c -> not present in set -> { 'a', 'c' }
    a -> present in set -> count=2 , set{} -> set{'a'}
    b -> not present in set -> set{'a','b'}
    a -> present in set -> count=3, set{} -> set{'a'}

    now traversing ends
    but set is not empty, so this will also make a substring
    Hence count++ -> count=4

    result  = 4
*/
class Solution {
    public int partitionString(String s) {
        char[] arr = s.toCharArray();

        int count = 0;
        Set<Character> set = new HashSet<>();
        for(char e : arr){

            // If character found in set
            if(set.contains(e)){
                // increase the counter
                count++;

                // make set empty
                set = new HashSet<>();
            }
            set.add(e);
        }

        // If something present in the set, then that will also make a substring
        if(!set.isEmpty()) count++;

        return count;
    }
}
```

