Straight forward greedy, add as much as possible into current partition, that'll also make next partition much easier.
[7ms submission](https://leetcode.com/submissions/detail/798176446/)
# Bitmask
```java
class Solution {
    public int partitionString(String s) {
        int res = 1, mask = 0; // at least 1 partition
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            int maskc = 1 << (c-'a');
            // if ((mask >> (c-'a') & 1) == 1) {
            if ((maskc & mask) > 0) { // this char has already been used in cur partition
                mask = maskc; // start a new partition with cur char
                res++; // count the new partition
            } else mask |= maskc; // add cur char to cur partition
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```
# Boolean Array
if bitmask is not user friendly, you could also use boolean array
