# Intuition
First determine, how you have to create substrings based on the problem description.

# Approach
Traverse the string and start adding the elements in the set if it's not already present. As soon as you encounter the element which is already present in the set, then make a partition.
We are creating partitions hypothetically, just by clearing the set and increasing the value of the count variable as soon as we encounter any element which is already present in the set. Repeat this process until we iterate over the entire string.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)

- Space complexity: O(1)
In worst case, we might need to store all the disticnt characters in the Hashset, which actually is a constant value. So, space complexity is constant.

