# Intuition


My first thought was to iterate the complete string and keep track of each character which should be unique and at the time when any character repeat increment the answer value and erase the map and continue the process again. 

# Approach
1. Create a map of type <char,int>.
2. Create variable ans and initiate it with 0.
3. Now, Travese each character of string one by one and increment its count in map to track it's occurance.
4. At the time if you get the count of the character, it mean that the character is already been traverse in the currebt substring.
5. Increment the answer and erase the map.
6. The same process will be repeated for the remanining part.
7. At last when entire string will be traversed then then return the final answer with one incremented for the last substring. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(n)

- Space complexity: O(1)

![IMG_20230406_001856.jpg](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/f3d48ea7-8f5e-4651-a67d-72348d60525e_1680720828.8575788.jpeg)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int partitionString(string s) {
        unordered_map<char,int> mp;
        int ans=0;
        for(int i=0;i<s.size();i++)
        {
            if(!mp.count(s[i]))
            {
                mp[s[i]]++;
            }  
            else
            {
                ans++;
                mp.erase(mp.begin(),mp.end());
                mp[s[i]]++;
            }
        }
        return (ans+1);
    }
};
```

