# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Using int array of length 26 to store the number of occurences of characters.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The int array `arr[26]` is to store the number of occurence of the alphabet in the string. For example, the arr works like 
```
s = "abd";
arr = [1, 1, 0 ,1, 0, 0, 0, 0...]
      (a)(b)(c)(d)(e)(f)(g)(h)...
```

If the number of occurence of a character is not equal to zero, it implies that the character is already present. So, the array is set to zero again and the sub string count is incremented by 1.



# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int partitionString(String s) {
        char characters[] = s.toCharArray();
        int arr[] = new int[26];
        int count = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < characters.length; i++) {
            char c = characters[i];
            if(arr[c - 'a'] != 0) {
                count++;
                Arrays.fill(arr,0);
                arr[c - 'a']++;
            } 
            arr[c - 'a']++;
        }
        return ++count;
    }
}
```

