# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- Make a map to store the frequency of a character of substring****
(keep in mind we are talking about the frequency of a substring not the whole given string) .
- traverse over the given string ```s``` and:
- i) check if the current index's ```character``` has occured in map ```nakhsa``` or not. If it does not exist store it into ```naksha```  and increase the traversal pointer ```i```. This means we are considering that character in a substring as this character has not occured before in the ```substring```.

- - ii) If the current index's character has occured before in the same substring, then raise the ```result/ counter``` by one, which  means we can not accomodate duplicate characters in the same substring again and wee need another substring form now-onwards to store the remaining characters. 
 here in this string ----------->  ```"ab|ac|ab|a"``` 
we break the substring at index 2( the moment we again get a within the same subtring and increase the counter by 1) and so on
- - ii.1) Also``` earse the map frequency``` if we encounter duplicate characters again, so that fresh frequency of next characters could be stored again for``` new substrings``` ahead.



# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(N) as we traverse over the string only once throughout

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(N) for map

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int partitionString(string s) {
        int i=0; // starting index
        int n= s.size();
        unordered_map<int, int> naksha;
        int count=0;
        while(i<n){
            if(naksha[s[i]]==0){
                naksha[s[i]]++; // if the character do not exist already upto now in the string, then update its frequency in map and consider it in a valid substring
                i++; // and also increment the traversal pointer
            }
            else{ // else if within the same substring(jisme traverse karte karte hum current index par pahuche hai) contains same character twice, then break the string by increasing the 'count' variable and clear the map so that next substring's character could be tracked in map
                count++; 
                naksha.clear();
            }
        }
        return count+1;
    }
};
```
