# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Declare a HashSet of Characters and then intialize a count with value 0. Now we will iterate over each character of the string and check if that chacacter is already present in the array if it is already present then increase the count and clear the hashset so that it can again start collecting new unique character.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int partitionString(String s) {
        HashSet<Character> hs = new HashSet<>();
        int count = 0;
        for(int i = 0 ; i < s.length(); i ++){
            //char at that index present in the hashset
            if(hs.contains(s.charAt(i))){
                //increase the count by 1
                count++;
                //clear the hashset so that it can again start collecting new unique char.
                hs.clear();
            }
            hs.add(s.charAt(i));
        }
        //returning count + 1 because we are counting total cuts in 
        //the string and we need to return total new substrings
        return count+1;
    }
}
```
