# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
* The intuition behind the code is to use an unordered_set to store the characters in each substring. The unordered_set is a data structure that allows us to quickly check if a character is already in the set. If the character is already in the set, then we know that it has already been used in a previous substring. In this case, we increment the counter and clear the unordered_set. This ensures that each substring will contain only unique characters.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1) Create an unordered_set to store the characters in each substring.
2) Initialize a counter to 1.
3) Iterate over the characters in the string.
4) If the current character is already in the unordered_set, then increment the counter and clear the unordered_set.
5) Otherwise, add the current character to the unordered_set.
6) Repeat steps 3-5 until the end of the string is reached.
7) Return the counter.
